This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques applied to social media data, specifically Twitter. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves dimensionality reduction and clustering, which are techniques commonly used in unsupervised learning, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) likely categories as well. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category. Finally, the paper involves optimization of hyperparameters, which could place it in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category.
